@tiw Sure! php_token_stream autoloader is required in the `phpunit/php-code-coverage` package through a `require_once`

https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/php-code-coverage/blob/master/PHP/CodeCoverage/Autoload.php#L47

What makes it fail is that Composer uses `require` for the `files` key and `include` for the classes loaded through the `psr-0` key, in the `composer.json` file.

I'm having issues with this too and just like @theUniC said. Composer is using require instead of require_once, and they seem unwilling to go for require_once, arguing that the loader should only be included once, and that require_once is heavier.

I would argue that the performance gain from using require vs require_once is miniscule and a bad case of premature micro optimization. But you PHPUnit could implement an include guard in all its autoloaders, like @tiw mentions.

``` PHP
if (!function_exists('php_tokenstream_autoload')) { 
    function php_tokenstream_autoload($class = NULL) { /* ... */ }
}

/* or if function_exists is to heavy ... */

if (!defined('PHPUNIT_TOKENSTREAM_INCLUDED')) {
    define('PHPUNIT_TOKENSTREAM_INCLUDED', true) 
    function php_tokenstream_autoload($class = NULL) { /* ... */ }
}

```
